  <releases>
    <release version="0.6" date="2022-06-20">
      <description>
        <p>Added:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Support for verbose/quiet mode</li>
          <li>Support for setting manual verbosity level</li>
          <li>Command-line options for verbose/qeiet mode and manual verbosity level</li>
          <li>Command-line option --version</li>
          <li>Wider application window on first launch</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Fixed:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Welcome message could not contain single qoutes</li>
          <li>Login Manager (GDM) broke on systems with SELinux enabled (mainly Fedora)</li>
          <li>Maximized or big application window looked bad (content was much smaller than the window)</li>
          <li>Showed wrong destination directory/folder path while extracting default shell theme</li>
          <li>Clicking 'Apply' did nothing if selected background image was deleted before applying</li>
          <li>Clicking 'Apply' applied only some settings on Ubuntu</li>
        </ul>
        <p>New Translations:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>French</li>
          <li>Hebrew</li>
          <li>Persian</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Updated Translations:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Dutch</li>
          <li>German</li>
          <li>Occitan</li>
          <li>Spanish</li>
          <li>Urdu</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
  </releases>

